cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.SY, cs.FL 

The paper discusses the fusion of artificial neural networks and fuzzy inference systems, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence and machine learning. Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of these techniques in engineering and real-world problem-solving, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.FL (Fuzzy Logic).
